Subject: workspace-mcp: always show account picker + pass login_hint

Two related UX fixes for the Google consent flow:

1. Always pass `prompt="select_account consent"` on the authorization
   URL, overriding upstream's `_determine_oauth_prompt()` choice.
   Upstream picks `"consent"` (no picker) when no cached credentials
   exist for the given email — but that's exactly the first-login
   case where the user most needs an account picker. Without the
   picker, Google uses whichever Google session the browser already
   has, which is usually the wrong account for a Cloud project.

2. Pass `login_hint=user_google_email` when the caller already named
   an account, so Google pre-selects it on the picker and the user
   can always click "Use a different account" to escape.

Upstream equivalent for (2): github.com/taylorwilsdon/google_workspace_mcp PR #556.
(1) has no upstream PR yet — a stronger default than upstream's per-state logic.

See: docs/adr/0003-direct-google-api-over-n8n.md

--- a/auth/google_auth.py
+++ b/auth/google_auth.py
@@ -515,7 +515,19 @@ async def start_auth_flow(
             required_scopes=current_scopes,
             session_id=session_id,
         )
-        auth_url, _ = flow.authorization_url(access_type="offline", prompt=prompt_type)
+        # LazyClaw patch: (1) always force `select_account consent` so
+        # Google shows an account picker even on first-time consent —
+        # upstream's `_determine_oauth_prompt` returns plain "consent"
+        # when no creds are cached for the email, which skips the
+        # picker entirely and opens on whichever Google session the
+        # browser already has. (2) pass `login_hint` when the caller
+        # named an account, so the picker pre-selects it and the
+        # user can always click "Use a different account" to escape.
+        # See ADR-0003.
+        auth_kwargs = {"access_type": "offline", "prompt": "select_account consent"}
+        if user_google_email:
+            auth_kwargs["login_hint"] = user_google_email
+        auth_url, _ = flow.authorization_url(**auth_kwargs)

